xmlconfig.Description: Determines the amount of tax associated with the transaction using Taxware.
xmlconfig.Author: MetraTech Corp. (Engineering)

ptype.description: This account will be examined to determine country and country zone. This will then be used with parameter tables containing Taxware rates and other information to determine the tax rate.
The amount that should be taxed.
This is the date of the transaction. The date is used to select the best fitting rate from the Taxware parameter tables.
The interval ID associated with the transaction.
A code identifying the product. Not used by Taxware.
If true, the amount already includes the tax. This field may be left blank and the value from GeneralConfig will be used.

The rounding algorithm to use. Acceptable values are: NONE or BANK. NONE means no rounding will be performed. BANK means banker's rounding will be performed. This field may be left blank and the value from GeneralConfig will be used.
The number of rounding digits. 0 - no rounding, 1 round to 1 digit after decimal point, 2 for 2 digits, etc. This field may be left blank and the value from GeneralConfig will be used.
The name of the customer for which we are computing taxes.
